cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DS 

The paper deals with program analysis and verification techniques for concurrent programs, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The use of resource parameters and the focus on context-unbounded analysis suggest a connection to the logic (cs.LO) and concurrency (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of examples and case studies suggests a possible connection to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
